data.description: Privately tucked amongst majestic cedars, a sweet spot to call home...just in time to enjoy Whidbey's gorgeous summer months. All you need is your favorite book, flip flops, and your willingness to leave city life behind. Freshly painted interior w/new carpet & community amenities of pvt. beach, clubhouse, pool, tennis&basketball courts, boat ramp & more. Big Gig Fiberoptic internet. An affordable opportunity to secure Whidbey property while enjoying simple island living. Live Work Play Whidbey!

responsivePhotos.caption: Sun dappled and ready for summertime fun and relaxation. Sweet single wide, move in ready. Enjoy simple island living!
Street view. Front window belongs to the kitchen. Plenty of space to park with a low maintenance yard to enjoy.
Tucked away in a cedar grove, enjoy the peace & beauty of nature right outside your front door.
As you step through the covered front entrance, this sweet gem of a home will surprise you with the spaciousness living/kitchen area and all of the fresh updates.

Looking back at the front covered entrance (opened door) from the living room into the kitchen. Behind the opened door is a closet.  Living room boasts two large windows so you can continue to admire the cedars from inside.
Well thought out kitchen design with a breakfast bar and built in dining table. There is another door from the kitchen to the outside (see far center of photo).

View from kitchen door (to outside).  Lots of cupboard space! This well loved and well tended home has everything you need to settle into Whidbey living.  A 15 minute drive to the ferry makes for an easy commute.
Newer stainless oven/range with brand new overhead vent.
Built in work station provides a convenient desk space where you can enjoy the benefit of fiberoptic internet service available to this neighborhood. Makes working from home easy!
Keep it simple. Pull up a chair and enjoy a glass of wine or a game of Backgammon. Kitchen has built in dining table and breakfast bar, all you need is a couple of chairs & barstools.
Another view of the living room that is open to the kitchen.  Hallway to the right leads to the two bedrooms, laundry area, and full bath.  Follow the new carpet to the cozy back half of this home.

Straight ahead, entrance to master bedroom, doorway in the forefront on the left is to the 2nd bedroom, across from the washer/dryer is another door to the outdoors.Entrance to bath is between washer & dryer.
Newer washer & dryer with storage cabinets above. Entrance to full bath is to your left and to the right you catch a glimpse of the master bedroom.
Master bedroom with closet space and two windows.  To photographer's back is an entrance into the full bath.

View of master from hallway door. Note the built in dresser space with mirror.  No need for bedroom furniture, just bring your bed along with those kitchen chairs and you've got yourself a sweet spot on Whidbey!
Another view from within the master bedroom.

Full bath.  Updated shower/tub is to the left and the toilet is out of view to the right of the photographer.  Photographer is standing in the hallway entrance to the bath with the door to the right leading to the master bedroom.
The 2nd Bedroom, a cozy space that could also serve as an office space or guest space. There is closet in this bedroom as well.
Patio space and level yard allow for plenty of space for a picnic table or even a fire pit.  Such privacy for a lot this size.
What the cedars see.....
This lot would also make a great building lot in the future.  Buy & enjoy now and built that stick built home in the years to come.  A great way to secure a Whidbey home.
Take a deep breath and relax into Island Time.  Sometimes less is more.
Another view of this cozy home.  Note the stairs on the right lead into the kitchen.

The community amenities are generous at Scatchet Head.  The indoor pool & clubhouse are seen here. The clubhouse can be reserved for gatherings and celebrations.  There is a pool table in the clubhouse.
Adjacent to the clubhouse is a large grassy field with a playscape and a covered BBQ pavilion which is also available to you for group gatherings & celebrations. HOA dues are $450/year
Basketball at the beach! Tennis courts are adjacent to the basketball court.  Discover the Play in Live Work Play Whidbey! www.scatchetheadclub.com for more info.
Ok, it's not just your flip flops & favorite book you'll want to bring.  How about crab pots and fishing poles? The community boat launch invites you to enjoy the endless gifts of Puget Sound!
Swim some laps or let the kids delight in the heated indoor pool that sits seaside with mountain views. Check out community website www.scatchetheadclub.com.
Steps from the pool, the clubhouse is a great place for a game of pool or for that next birthday party, baby shower or retirement celebration. Discover why so many love their Whidbey community.

Lose the flip flops and slow the pace. Allow the osprey, eagles, heron, sea lions, seals, orcas and grey whales to awe you along with the Olympic Mountains and Mt. Rainier.  Welcome to Whidbey. Welcome Home.
